TO RUN

cd '/Users/kevinorange/Downloads/Software Engineering/Maui'
./run-dev.sh


TO CONNECT AZURE SQL
In the API config:
1) Open GobTrackerApi/appsettings.Development.json
2) Keep both connection strings configured:
	- SqlDatabaseDefault (Active Directory Default)
	- SqlDatabaseInteractive (Active Directory Interactive)
3) Optional (recommended to reduce prompts): install Azure CLI and run az login before demo
4) Start the API first
5) In the app click "Show Players"
6) The app calls http://localhost:5117/api/players and displays Id, PlayerName, Team, Points
7) If Default auth has no token source, API falls back to Interactive sign-in


MILESTONE 1 CHECK
- MAUI app calls local API
- API reads from cloud SQL db
- MAUI displays records on screen




TO KILL
pkill -f MauiApp1
